reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Flexible and custom fit
reviews.reviewText: The size was adequate to allow trimming to fit a good range of waist. The belts need to be cut with hot metal to stop peeling. The belt loop is tedious to keep from loosing since it can not be fixed to the belt to allow cutting to length. I purchased the belts in a time that I was loosing weight. Worked perfect during this transition. They are firm and holding up well. Not as formal as leather belts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality and value
reviews.reviewText: Good value for these belts. Looks like they will hold up well too with frequent use. Perfect if you hate taking off your belt to pass through screening (no metal).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I really wasn't expecting these belts to work as well as they do. I didn't think the buckle would hold but it does and it holds all day. The belt is lightweight and durable, which is what I was looking for. Now I have to see how long they last. So far a very good deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice looking and a great value!
reviews.reviewText: These nylon belts are good strong nylon and they look nice, and do not stretch. The buckle seemed a bit cheep at first because it is molded plastic. But after cutting the belt to size and holding a fire to the cut edge to keep if from unraveling, I put it on and the buckle snapped closed tight and does not slip at all. These very inexpensive belts are great tactical/casual belts that you can adjust for a perfect fit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These belts can work well for cosmetic purposes, but not practical purposes. The buckles are made from cheap plastic, and can't seem to handle the job a belt is designed to do. The upshot: they are fine as an ornament.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Better than expected, great price and extremely durable. Very happy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I didn't really need three belts but for the price, WTH. These belts are sturdy and the buckles are great. They stay locked tight. Other nylon belts I've had in the past came with buckles that kept loosening. Not this belt. The buckle stays locked right where you close it. In fact, you have to kind of lift it outward when unbuckling to allow it to unlock. Not a big deal once you discover that. I am not crazy about the little elastic band that serves as the loop you pass the end through once you buckle it. It does hold the tail end of the belt just fine but when taking the belt off your pants, it will catch on the belt loop of your pants as you take the belt out. First couple of times, I fount the little elastic band on the floor. Now, I simply feed it through the pant belt loop as I begin to remove the belt so it doesn't do that. Not a big enough deal to deduct a star from my rating. The belt is also easy to adjust to a smaller waist size by cutting the end that locks into the buckle. Just know that with any nylon belt, you will have to melt the cut end with a match or lighter to prevent fraying. Just be careful with that and don't over heat it or catch it on fire. I even used one of these belts to strap a car battery onto the back of my bicycle when I had to ride to the auto parts store. The battery was too heavy for my bungee cords but the addition of this belt around it held it tight on my ride home!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Buckle function is slightly different from old school metal buckles of military belts.
reviews.reviewText: There is a bit of a learning curve with these plastic buckles. They seem very durable, my concern I would break them appear to have been unfounded. The buckle holds very firmly without the slipping that the metal buckles do. I'm sure in a few days I'll feel familiar with the new buckles and wonder why I tolerated the WWII Era design.
